Among all Central American countries, Costa Rica has the most trending and liberal attitudes towards divorce. No matter how this trend developed, in recent years, divorce rates have greatly multiplied. The number of divorces has significantly grown.

Getting married in Costa Rica usually equates to moving to the same city as the girl you’re courting. However, that doesn’t mean you can’t take matters into your hands if you’d want to marry your Costa Rican bride. Nevertheless, English isn’t widely spoken in the nation. It means you ought to learn Spanish, especially if you aren’t fluent in the language. If you’re serious about marrying your Costa Rican bride, learn and practice the language to exhibit your efforts.

Be respectful and polite when trying to win a Costa Rican bride’s heart. Costa Rican culture teaches people to respect the state institutions and authority figures regardless of other activities happening. For instance, you should use “dueno” when addressing someone in Costa Rica. While this expression alone lacks much meaning or negativity, it turns out disastrous if you pair it together with the expression “pago.” English speakers often incorrectly integrate the term “pago” into a sentence to mean “pay” or “paycheck.” You’re naturally expected to use the word “donation.” In Costa Rica, your sweetheart will feel overwhelmed by this move. It can add points for you in her heart.
